      "action_code": "H32020",
      "bill_ids": [
        "hres706-108"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "text": "House resolved itself into the Committee of the Whole House on the state of the Union pursuant to H. Res. 706 and Rule XVIII.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T13:16:42-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "references": [],
      "text": "GENERAL DEBATE - The Committee of the Whole proceeded with one hour of general debate on H.R. 3598.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T14:24:07-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "bill_ids": [
        "hres706-108"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "text": "DEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of H. Res. 706, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Jackson-Lee (TX) amendment.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T14:32:40-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "references": [],
      "text": "POSTPONED PROCEEDINGS - At the conclusion of debate on the Jackson-Lee (TX) amendment, the Chair put the question on adoption of the amendment and by voice vote, announced that the noes had prevailed. Ms. Jackson-Lee (TX) demanded a recorded vote and the Chair postponed further proceedings on the question of adoption of the amendment until later in the legislative day.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T14:33:47-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "bill_ids": [
        "hres706-108"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "text": "DEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of H. Res. 706, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Larson (CT) amendment.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T14:41:53-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "references": [],
      "text": "POSTPONED PROCEEDINGS - At the conclusion of debate on the Larson (CT) amendment the Chair put the question on adoption of the amendment and by voice vote, announced that the ayes had prevailed. Mr. Ehlers demanded a recorded vote and the Chair postponed further proceedings on the question of adoption of the amendment until later in the legislative day.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T14:42:51-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "bill_ids": [
        "hres706-108"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "text": "DEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of H. Res. 706, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 10 minutes of debate on the Peterson (PA) amendment.",
      "type": "action"
    },
    {
      "acted_at": "2004-07-09T14:46:21-04:00",
      "action_code": "H8D000",
      "bill_ids": [
        "hres706-108"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "text": "DEBATE - Pursuant to the provisions of H. Res. 706, the Committee of the Whole proceeded with 20 minutes of debate on the Gordon amendment.",
